# Triage Workflow

## When to Use

- A maintainer asks what needs triage attention.
- A specific issue or PR needs categorisation and state progression.
- You need to prepare an item for autonomous implementation.

## Core Approach

Read and follow `.github/skills/triage/SKILL.md` exactly.

Key points:

- Maintain exactly one category role and one state role.
- Verify bug/PR claims before recommending `ready-for-agent` when possible.
- Use `.github/skills/triage/AGENT-BRIEF.md` for `ready-for-agent` handoff comments.
- Use `.github/skills/triage/OUT-OF-SCOPE.md` when rejecting enhancements as `wontfix`.
- Prefix every triage-generated tracker comment with the AI disclaimer from the skill.

## Skill Files

- `.github/skills/triage/SKILL.md`
- `.github/skills/triage/AGENT-BRIEF.md`
